{{short description|A temporary ocean surface current. It is an extension of the Guinea Current, flowing near western Africa's coast}}
'''Angola current''' is a temporary ocean surface [[Ocean current|current]]. It is an extension of the [[Guinea Current]], flowing near western Africa's coast. It is known to have created similar effects in the [[upwelling]] as [[El Niño]],<ref>http://oceancurrents.rsmas.miami.edu/atlantic/angola.html</ref> though its effect is weaker.

