[[File:Zagreb 1 Ilica.jpg|thumb|300px|Ilica near Ban Jelačić Square]] '''Ilica street''' is one of the longest streets in [[Zagreb]], [[Croatia]]. The busy street is home to many shops and cultural sites and spans through most of the northwestern part of the city, from the [[Ban Jelačić Square]] in the [[city centre]] westward to the [[Vrapče, Zagreb|Vrapče]] district. The street is 5.66 km long, making it the third longest street in the city.<ref name="JL">{{cite web | url=http://www.jutarnji.hr/vijesti/zagreb/ulice-koje-zbunjuju-postare-spajaju-parove-i-izluduju-susjede/2862398/ | title=Ulice koje zbunjuju poštare, spajaju parove i izluđuju susjede | date=20 July 2009 | language=Croatian | accessdate=2017-04-24}}</ref>
The name was first recorded in 1431,<ref>http://www.vecernji.hr/moj-kvart/ovo-nije-najduza-ulica-ali-je-najzagrebackija-900941</ref> while the street itself retained its present shape at the end of the 18th century. In the 14th century, the street was known under the name ''Lončarska ves'' (archaic Croatian for "Potters' village", also ''Vicus lutifigulorum'' in [[Latin language|Latin]]).<ref name="hawkesworth">{{cite book|last1=Hawkesworth|first1=Celia|title=Zagreb: A Cultural and Literary History|date=2007|publisher=[[Signal Books]]|isbn=9781904955306|page=31|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eBSxMUKFJDEC&pg=PA31&lpg=PA31&dq=vla%C5%A1ka+zagreb+history&source=bl&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=vla%C5%A1ka%20zagreb%20history&f=false|language=en}}</ref>
==Notable addresses== *{{0}}1 Ilica Street - The [[1 Ilica Street]] skyscraper *{{0}}3 Ilica Street - [[Croatian Bureau of Statistics]] *{{0}}5 Ilica Street - Palace of the [[First Croatian Savings Bank]] with [[Oktogon (Zagreb)|Oktogon]] *{{0}}7 Ilica Street - [[Metropolitanate of Zagreb, Ljubljana and all Italy]] *12 Ilica Street - [[British Council]] in Zagreb *17 Ilica Street - The [[Tošo Dabac]] Archive *36 Ilica Street - [[Plavi telefon]] (Blue Phone), [[helpline]] for children and youth *48 Ilica Street - [[Democratic Centre (Croatia)|Democratic Centre]] party headquarters *85 Ilica Street - [[Academy of Fine Arts Zagreb|Zagreb Academy of Fine Arts]] *208 Ilica Street - [[EXIT Theater Zagreb|EXIT Theater]]
